---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageIntro from '../../components/PageIntro.astro';
import { capabilities, experiences } from '../../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout title="Quantitative Research and Trading" description="Production-focused quantitative research across forecasting, market making, execution, market data, monitoring, and risk.">
  <div class="shell">
    <PageIntro eyebrow="Profile / production markets" title="Quantitative Research and Trading" description="I build short-horizon forecasting, execution, market-making, and research infrastructure from data and simulation through monitoring and risk." />
  </div>

  <section class="section" id="experience">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">Experience</p><h2>Research connected to live systems.</h2></div>
        <p>Each card keeps the mandate concise and links to public or sanitized evidence. Employer data, exact parameters, live positions, and reconstructable strategy logic are excluded.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="entry-list">
        {experiences.map((experience) => (
          <article class="experience-card" id={experience.id}>
            <div class="experience-meta">
              <strong>{experience.organization}</strong>
              <span>{experience.dates}</span><br />
              <span>{experience.location}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="experience-body">
              <h2>{experience.role}</h2>
              <p>{experience.mandate}</p>
              <ul class="impact-list">{experience.accomplishments.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}</ul>
              <div class="tech-row">{experience.technologies.map((technology) => <span>{technology}</span>)}</div>
              <div class="button-row"><a class="button button-secondary" href={experience.evidenceHref}>Inspect supporting evidence</a></div>
            </div>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="capabilities">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">Capabilities</p><h2>Organized by system.</h2></div>
        <p>The relevant question is not whether a tool appears in a list. It is which part of a research and production system that tool supports.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="capability-grid">
        {capabilities.map(([title, text]) => <article class="capability"><h3>{title}</h3><p>{text}</p></article>)}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="independent-projects">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">Independent systems</p><h2>Research beyond the role description.</h2></div>
        <p>Historical crypto market-making work and the IMC Prosperity challenge remain supporting projects. Detailed claims will be added only with documentation and reproducible artifacts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card"><p class="eyebrow">Crypto infrastructure</p><h3>Market-making research stack</h3><p>Exchange feeds, fee-aware fill simulation, monitoring, and high-speed research loops across Python, Polars, Numba, PyTorch, and Rust.</p></article>
        <article class="card"><p class="eyebrow">Competition</p><h3>IMC Prosperity 4</h3><p>Algorithmic trading challenge work placed in the top 3% of more than 6,000 teams.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
